<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1927,2025]" box="[151,844,1927,1952]" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,244,1927,1952]" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[323,458,1928,1952]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="361" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.3 mm</quantity>
(n=4); female: 2.8–3.0 mm (n=3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1927,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1964,1989]" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">Morphology.</emphasis>
Crown longer than distance between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[873,940,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1007,1029]" captionTargetBox="[239,1346,212,991]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,193,993]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cortona minuta A, male habitus, dorsal view; B, brachypterous female habitus, dorsal view; C, male habitus, lateral view; D, brachypterous female habitus, lateral view; E, male face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376437/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B). Male anteclypeus distinctly tapered distally (
<figureCitation box="[249,312,2000,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1007,1029]" captionTargetBox="[239,1346,212,991]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,193,993]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Cortona minuta A, male habitus, dorsal view; B, brachypterous female habitus, dorsal view; C, male habitus, lateral view; D, brachypterous female habitus, lateral view; E, male face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376437/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="361">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376437/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="362" targetBox="[239,1346,212,991]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1007,1060]" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1007,1029]" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[287,450,1008,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[287,450,1008,1030]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">Cortona minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A, male habitus, dorsal view; B, brachypterous female habitus, dorsal view; C, male habitus, lateral view; D, brachypterous female habitus, lateral view; E, male face.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376438/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="362" targetBox="[262,1327,1124,1911]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1950,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1950,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[283,445,1951,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[283,445,1951,1973]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="362">Cortona minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C, valve, ventral view D, subgenital plate, ventral view; E, style, dorsal view; F, G, H, connective and aedeagus, dorsal, ventral and lateral view, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate short, lateral margin distinctly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1093,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[262,1327,1124,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[242,1342,1084,1934]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cortona minuta A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve, ventral view D, subgenital plate, ventral view; E, style, dorsal view; F, G, H, connective and aedeagus, dorsal, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376438/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D). Style with articulating arm long; preapical lobe angulate; apophysis short, strongly laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1107,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[262,1327,1124,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[242,1342,1084,1934]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cortona minuta A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve, ventral view D, subgenital plate, ventral view; E, style, dorsal view; F, G, H, connective and aedeagus, dorsal, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376438/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
E). Connective shorter than aedeagus. Aedeagus broadly and deeply bifid apically, with pair of slender appendages directed apicad on dorsal surface, curved away from each other and not extended to shaft apex, distal depressed portion of shaft with pair of small lateral teeth directed basad subapically (
<figureCitation box="[668,734,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1972]" captionTargetBox="[262,1327,1124,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[242,1342,1084,1934]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cortona minuta A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve, ventral view D, subgenital plate, ventral view; E, style, dorsal view; F, G, H, connective and aedeagus, dorsal, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376438/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
F–H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Female abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with median lobe overlapping slightly more than half total width of posterior margin, trilobed, median lobe acutely pointed and slightly longer and narrower than lateral lobes, darkly pigmented (
<figureCitation box="[159,239,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1279,1301]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,205,1232]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[188,1398,193,1258]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Females of Cortona: A – D, Cortona minuta: A, first valvula; B, detail of first valvula apex; C, second valvula; D, third valvula. E – I, abdominal sternite VII: E, C. minuta; F, C. catanachae; G, C. silvai; H, C. otamendiensis; I, C. concordica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376448/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
